Btw, as long as this is, keep in mind, I was extremely bored! :P  I'm not psycho, much.<br>
<br>
I think when people are writing their posts here, they are writing as if they are holding a conversation rather than writing a formal document (First sentence; main point, the rest is fluff).  Spelling and grammar are important in a persons formal education and important in many other situations, but improper spelling and grammar does not constitute a lack of intelligence.  When dealing with resumes, it is standard that it should be spotless, or else -  you are the weakest link, goodbye! <br>
<br>
When I was in high school, I did not do well in grammar class for two main reasons: <br>
1). I did not care and 2). I did not care for my teacher.  Did that make me stupid?  No.  There are many other reasons why I am stupid :P.  In fact, there are many people that would have been great in societys eyes, had they not had the teacher telling them they were worthless and stupid.  In fact, there have been.  Not everyone is so fortunate though.  Some may take it with a grain of salt, and others may truly feel they are a disappointment and failure, leading to pre-adult conflicts and problems, onto and into their future adult lives.  That disgusts me.    But I digress.  <br>
<br>
The very first and single most important class I had in college was ENG101A Grammar Fundamentals (something like that), a pre-requisite to ENG101 Freshman College Composition.  That class helped me through every single paper I had to write while working on my bachelors.  During my time in college, there were people that did not have to take a grammar class as a pre-requisite, because they tested out of it or the college did not require it.  One thing I have learned through meeting all the different people I did is, just because I may be able to convey my thoughts on paper more effectively then others, does not make me more intelligent than them.  <br>
<br>
There are people that cannot speak for damn, but can write like a novelist.  There are people that cannot write for damn, but can speak and debate like Plato.  I met several people just like this; very intelligent people, but they were not very good writers.  They just could not convey their thoughts onto paper as well as others may have been able to.  I can theorize all I want about why; like maybe they are lazy or maybe the right side of their brain functions more efficiently than the left (or vice/versa  cannot remember what side is responsible for what :P), but it does not make them stupid.  <br>
<br>
Anyway, there is a time for formalities and time for fun.  This place is supposed to be fun.  I am not telling anyone how to judge other people  he without sin, cast the first stone.  Judge them how you like.  I just cannot see how you can assume someone is less intelligent than yourself, just because you are more eloquent in how you conduct your phrase, and by basis of your educational background being more diverse.  For some people, it may take an entire book to simply call someone else a jackass.  For others, they may simply come out and call you a jackass.  Either way, you are still a jackass :P.  This is not directed at anyone, just writing down some thoughts I am having.  <br>
<br>
On a side note, who you are in society also depends on the circle of people you are with.  I stress in society, not in your own being.  That means, if I hang with a bunch of druggies all the time, people assume Im a druggie, but I may not be.  It could just be I like those people; I grew up with them or whatever (its only and example, dont get crazy!  I know its not the best).  So there are people in the so-called hated guilds around here that I actually like, and hang with and group with, whether the EQ society likes them or not.  That does not change who I am and will not change my friendship with them.  In fact, I really do not hate any of the guilds on the server.  For one it is a game, and two, when Ive been wronged, it is usually because of a certain individual or few, not the entire guild.  Sometimes an entire guild may be responsible for your demise, because that is the force and numbers it took, but really it is due to a few key people.  The rest are just following along for whatever reasons they have.<br>
<br>
Also, I notice that many people here are very competitive.  There is nothing wrong with that.  In this nation we are brought up to compete; get the better grades, get the better job, make more money, win more championships, etc  Just remember, denial is not just a river in Egypt.  What that means is, if I say FU a thousand times and you continue to write paragraph, upon paragraph about how stupid I am, because all I am saying is FU, then you my friend are the perceived sucker  figure it out.  Disclaimer  that is the case only sometimes - I am not saying that is the case all the time, because truly, there are some jackasses out there, which really have nothing better to say than FU.  Then again, they may just be egging you on.  The main point, without all the fluff is; you may just continue to outwit these persons based on the fact you are competitive and feel like you need to show you are the smarter one.  I could be wrong, because most of the time, I am J  <br>
<br>
Also, with the IT age, comes a new type of bully I have noticed.  Before in school, when we were kids (some are still kids here), there were the popular people or the school bullies who may have picked on people for whatever reason it was, just because they could.  The new type of bully is the IT bully.  The technologically advanced or not so advanced :P, that can bully someone else based on his or her computer skills, educational background, or quite simply, their wits.  Is there a difference?  Physically the damage may not be as great, but mentally, it may be the same.  The ones that picked on the kids were wrong.  The ones that followed, well, they were followers.  There is nothing wrong with followers either, other wise we would have too many chiefs, and not enough Indians.<br>
<br>
In fact, where I work, there is an IT bully.  He is the smartest computer guy in the world that never has any time to help anyone, because we must bow down to his superior intelligence in the realm of computer technology.  Lol, he scares me.  Hes real funny too, drinks like a fish, and if you need help, you can find him at the club around the corner, just page him J.  If it were legal, I believe he would accept beer as compensation for work, rather than salary.  So would I though!  <br>
<br>
Thanks for reading; youve been a great crowd.  I know youre out there, I can hear you breathing!  - and Im outta here!<br>
